# trits2text: decode a stream of +0- trit-strings (whitespace-separated) to text.
# ; reads one token into a cell, [!;] prints it as a char and reads the next.
# '!' is the residue print: it renders a cell as its mod-243 byte (0..242), so
# the decode covers 0..242 (z and UTF-8 included) and round-trips text2trits.
# ASCII 0..121 is identical to '.'; only the 122..242 band differs.
;[!;]
